\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. DICHOTOMAE (Rohrb.) Chowdhuri. Annuals; stems erect, pubescent. Inflorescence branched, composed of raceme-like monochasial cymes. Calyx contracted at mouth in fruit, with prominent simple veins. Seeds reniform, with plane or slightly concave, tuberculate faces, and bluntly tuberculate back.
