\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 170. S. dichotoma }Ehrh., {\i Beitr. Naturk.}{\b  7}: 143 (1792). ({\i S. mathei} Pénzes). Stems 20-100 cm, branched above, puberulent to hispid-pubescent. Lower leaves spathulate to lanceolate; cauline lanceolate. Inflorescence usually with alar flowers- branches 5- to 10-flowered; pedicels all very short; upper bracts small, ovate, with scarious margins. Calyx 7-15 mm, ovoid-oblong in fruit, not inflated, sparsely and shortly pubescent between veins, sparsely hispid on veins; teeth ovate-lanceolate, acute. Petal-limb 7-8 mm, white, rarely pink; filaments and styles very long-exserted. Carpophore 1·5-4 mm, very stout, glabrous. Seeds 1·1-1·4 mm, blackish-brown. 2n = 24.{\i  Native in S. & E. Europe; widely naturalized elsewhere}. Bu Cr Gr Hu It Ju Rm Rs(B, C, W, K, E) Tu [Be Co Cz Ga Ge He Hs Po Rs(N) Su].
\par 

