\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 174. S. micropetala }Lag., {\i Gen. Sp. Nov.} 15 (1816). Like {\b 173} but calyx 10-15 mm, cuneate-subclavate in fruit; veins usually anastomosing above; petal-limb up to 3 mm, white or pink; capsule 9-10 mm, oblong; carpophore 3-4 mm; seeds with striate faces and less strongly tuberculate back. 2n = 24. {\i C. & S. Spain, Portugal.} Hs Lu.
