\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 175. S. discolor }Sm. in Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1}: 292 (1809) ({\i S. pompeiopolitana} Gay ex Boiss.). Like {\b 173} but stems and calyx with both long, soft hairs and short, glandular hairs; plant never villous; calyx 10-12 mm; petal-limb 4-6 mm, pink above, greenish beneath; capsule 7-8 mm; carpophore 4 mm; seeds 0·4-0·6 mm, chestnut-brown; faces very finely striate; back narrow, concave or grooved with a median row of low tubercles.{\i  Maritime sands. Karpathos}. Cr. ({\i E. Mediterranean region}.)
